	<section id="recipe">
		<p>
			The challenge when making clean recipes for 
			notoriously high-sugar and high-fat dishes (such as
			bread pudding) is to find magic healthy ingredients to
			replace all those unhealthy ones.	
			In this recipe, that magic ingredient happened to be
			cauliflower. 
			Yes sir, this was some magic indeed! Don't refuse it
			until you try it.
		</p>
		<table class="ingredients">
			<caption>Ingredients</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">amount</th>
					<th class="name">name</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.25"></td>
				<td class="unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="name">
					<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B00BFIVOZG/?tag=lich048-20" class="amazon">Perfect Fit vanilla vegan protein powder</a>
					<span class="altor">or</span> 
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.25"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="alt name">
					any vanilla- or toffee-flavoured protein powder
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.5"></td>
				<td class="unit">cups</td>
				<td class="name">steamed cauliflower</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.25"></td>
				<td class="unit">cup</td>
				<td class="name">liquid egg whites</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.5"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">
					<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B000KENKZ8/?tag=lich048-20" class="amazon">Bob's Red Mill coconut flour</a>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.25"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">natural vanilla essence</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1.25"></td>
				<td class="unit">drops</td>
				<td class="name">
					<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B001EO5RF4/?tag=lich048-20" class="amazon">Sweet Leaf liquid Stevia English toffee</a>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">whole</td>
				<td class="name">fresh strawberries</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.25"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">cinnamon</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount= "0.5"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="alt name">maple syrup (optional, for sweetness)</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<div class="servings">
			Servings: 
			<input id="servings" type="number" min="0" step="1" value="4" onchange="changeservings(this.value);" />
			(Total Calories: <span data-lilachop-amount="105"></span>.)
		</div>
		<p>
			This surprisingly simple and unusual recipe was
			adapted from 
			<a href="http://proteinpow.com/2012/09/is-it-protein-bread-pudding-is-it.html">Proteinpow Protein Bread Pudding</a> 
			by Anna Sward, the protein genius and my source of
			inspiration for clean, protein-packed recipes.  
			(She called it cross between bread pudding and french
			toast. Do you agree, my Choppers?)	
		</p>
		<table id="steps">
			<caption>Steps</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">time</th>
					<th>instruction</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Put aside the cinnamon, maple syrup and
					strawberries for last.
				</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td> 
					Blend all other ingredients together in a
					high-speed blender until smooth (make
					sure there are no lumpy cauliflower
					bits).  
				</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">35</td>
				<td class="unit">min</td>
				<td>
					Pour into 4 muffin cups in a silicone
					muffin pan and bake at 160'C (320'F).
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Sprinkle muffins with cinnamon and
					maple syrup, and garnish with fresh
					strawberries.	
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">45</td>
				<td class="unit">min</td>
				<td>
					Devour!
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>
			This recipe serves 4, and macros are per sticky protein
			bread-pudding. (Admit it, those are some impressive
			macros, huh?) 
		</p>
		<p>
			<b>Recipe tip</b>: to make the recipe sugar-free, skip the
			maple syrup. However, if you find that you can
			still taste the cauliflower, simply add more cinnamon,
			maple syrup, and vanilla essence.	
		</p>
